9  2014  in Life at VMI  Slideshows Life at VMI Slideshows  by Kate Kate Kate Kate Kate Since its founding in 1839  VMI cadets have been bound by a code of honorable behavior  The cadet run Honor Court was established as a continuously operating body beginning in 1908  The heart of the VMI honor system is the Honor Code  A cadet does not lie  cheat  steal  nor tolerate those who do  Single Sanction The sanction for any breech of honor is dismissal  When rats sign the Matriculation Book  they commit themselves to a life of honesty and integrity  If their commitment is not complete  their stay at the Institute may be short  Trust Cadets live and learn in an environment of trust  Their daily lives and conduct are regulated by the traditions and rules of the Institute and a very simple code of honor  Cadets trust one another because their word is their bond  Conduct Above all else  cadets are expected to conduct themselves as men and women of character at all times  Exemplary conduct both at and away from the Institute reflects credit on the cadet  the Corps  and the Institute  Civility Cadets are expected commit to respectful living  treating everyone with dignity and fairness  Cadets come to understand the impact of their behavior on others and strive to exemplify civility  More about the Honor Code Since its founding in 1839  VMI cadets have been bound by a code of honorable behavior  The cadet run Honor Court was established as a continuously operating body beginning in 1908  The heart of the VMI honor system is the Honor Code  A cadet does not lie  cheat  steal  nor tolerate those who do Since its founding in 1839  VMI cadets have been bound by a code of honorable behavior  The cadet run Honor Court was established as a continuously operating body beginning in 1908  The heart of the VMI honor system is the Honor Code  A cadet does not lie  cheat  steal  nor tolerate those who do Since its founding in 1839  VMI cadets have been bound by a code of honorable behavior Since its founding in 1839  VMI cadets have been bound by a code of honorable behavior The cadet run Honor Court was established as a continuously operating body beginning in 1908  The heart of the VMI honor system is the Honor Code  A cadet does not lie  cheat  steal  nor tolerate those who do A cadet does not lie  cheat  steal  nor tolerate those who do Single Sanction The sanction for any breech of honor is dismissal  When rats sign the Matriculation Book  they commit themselves to a life of honesty and integrity  If their commitment is not complete  their stay at the Institute may be short  Trust Cadets live and learn in an environment of trust  Their daily lives and conduct are regulated by the traditions and rules of the Institute and a very simple code of honor  Cadets trust one another because their word is their bond  Conduct Above all else  cadets are expected to conduct themselves as men and women of character at all times  Exemplary conduct both at and away from the Institute reflects credit on the cadet  the Corps  and the Institute  Civility Cadets are expected commit to respectful living  treating everyone with dignity and fairness  Cadets come to understand the impact of their behavior on others and strive to exemplify civility  More about the Honor Code Single Sanction The sanction for any breech of honor is dismissal  When rats sign the Matriculation Book  they commit themselves to a life of honesty and integrity  If their commitment is not complete  their stay at the Institute may be short  Trust Cadets live and learn in an environment of trust  Their daily lives and conduct are regulated by the traditions and rules of the Institute and a very simple code of honor  Cadets trust one another because their word is their bond  Conduct Above all else  cadets are expected to conduct themselves as men and women of character at all times  Exemplary conduct both at and away from the Institute reflects credit on the cadet  the Corps  and the Institute  Civi